725778f-a.title: Queens: 109th Avenue - 128th Street
725778f-a.text:
109th Ave. (formerly Hawtree Creek Road), west from about
131st Street to 128th Street, where Hawtree Creek Road resumes its
Mname and continues southward. This set of two views shows the
W. Jellinghaus house of 1860 to 1873; later owned by Ditmars Van
Siclen. Wyckoff Van Siclen was an oocupant in 1922. In February
1925 the property was sold. St. Teresa's Catholic Church owned this
property in 1934.
1922.
Views 1 & 2.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
